## Guards — Auth from `@lib/auth`, Feature Guards Per Module

**Never write JWT or RBAC guards inside a feature module.** Import from `@lib/auth`.

| Guard | Source | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `UnifiedAuthGuard` | `@lib/auth` | JWT + API key + reCAPTCHA in one. Apply at controller class level. |
| `RolesGuard` | `@lib/auth` | Checks `user.user_roles`. Pair with `@RequireRoles()`. |
| `PermissionsGuard` | `@lib/auth` | Checks `user.permissions`. Pair with `@RequirePermissions()`. |
| `RoleGroupsGuard` | `@lib/auth` | Checks `user.role_groups`. Pair with `@RequireRoleGroups()`. |

| Decorator | Source | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `@CurrentUser()` | `@lib/auth` | Extracts `AuthUser` from `request.user` |
| `@RequireRoles(...roles)` | `@lib/auth` | Sets role metadata for `RolesGuard` |
| `@RequirePermissions(...perms)` | `@lib/auth` | Sets permission metadata for `PermissionsGuard` |
| `@Public()` | `@lib/auth` | Skips auth — add a comment explaining why |
| `@UseApiKey()` | `@lib/auth` | Forces API key auth even when JWT is present |

Feature-specific guards (e.g. "does this user own this order?") live in `presentation/guards/` but must not re-implement JWT or RBAC logic.

