## Response Envelope Contract

Every HTTP response uses one of two shapes, wired automatically by `CoreModule`:

| Outcome | Shape | Wired by |
|---------|-------|----------|
| **Success** | `SuccessResponse<T>` — `{ info, timestamp, traceId, responsePayload: T }` | `SuccessResponseInterceptor` (global, via `CoreModule`) |
| **Error** | `ErrorResponse` — `{ info, timestamp, traceId, messages[], errorCode?, status? }` | `GlobalExceptionFilter` (global, via `CoreModule`) |

**Consuming apps** register both via a single `CoreModule` import in their root `AppModule`:

```ts
// app.module.ts
@Module({ imports: [CoreModule, ...] })
export class AppModule {}
```

`CoreModule` is `@Global()` and registers:
- `APP_FILTER → GlobalExceptionFilter`
- `APP_INTERCEPTOR → SuccessResponseInterceptor`
- `APP_INTERCEPTOR → TimingInterceptor`

**Controllers return raw DTOs** — `SuccessResponse<T>` is applied transparently by the interceptor. Controllers must never construct `SuccessResponse` themselves.

---

## Swagger Response Decorators

Every controller method **must** declare both an explicit `Promise<T>` return type **and** one `@ApiAutoResponse*` decorator from `@lib/core`. These decorators document the final `SuccessResponse<T>` envelope shape in Swagger (matching what the interceptor actually returns at runtime).

| Scenario | Decorator | Example |
|----------|-----------|---------|
| Single DTO (GET by id, PATCH, DELETE returning DTO) | `@ApiAutoResponse(Dto)` | `@ApiAutoResponse(UserDto)` |
| POST creating a resource (201) | `@ApiAutoResponse(Dto, { status: 201 })` | `@ApiAutoResponse(OrderDto, { status: 201 })` |
| Paginated list — `PagedResponse<Dto>` | `@ApiAutoPagedResponse(Dto)` | `@ApiAutoPagedResponse(OrderDto)` |
| Flat array of DTOs | `@ApiAutoResponse(Dto, { isArray: true })` | `@ApiAutoResponse(RoleDto, { isArray: true })` |
| No payload / 204 | `@ApiAutoVoidResponse()` | `@ApiAutoVoidResponse({ status: 204 })` |
| Scalar primitive | `@ApiAutoPrimitiveResponse('boolean'\|'string'\|'number')` | `@ApiAutoPrimitiveResponse('boolean')` |
| Interface or primitive array (last resort) | Raw `@ApiOkResponse({ schema: ... })` | — |

All decorators are exported from `@lib/core`. Import path: `import { ApiAutoResponse, ApiAutoPagedResponse, ... } from '@lib/core'`.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — full example with all decorator types
@Get(':id')
@ApiAutoResponse(OrderDto)
getById(@Param('id') id: string): Promise<OrderDto> { ... }

@Post()
@ApiAutoResponse(OrderDto, { status: 201 })
create(@Body() dto: CreateOrderDto): Promise<OrderDto> { ... }

@Get()
@ApiAutoPagedResponse(OrderDto)
list(): Promise<PagedResponse<OrderDto>> { ... }

@Get('roles')
@ApiAutoResponse(RoleDto, { isArray: true })
listRoles(): Promise<RoleDto[]> { ... }

@Delete(':id')
@ApiAutoVoidResponse({ status: 204 })
delete(@Param('id') id: string): Promise<void> { ... }

@Delete('revoke/:id')
@ApiAutoPrimitiveResponse('boolean')
revoke(@Param('id') id: string): Promise<boolean> { ... }

// ❌ BAD — no return type, no Swagger decorator
async getUser(@Param('id') id: string) {
  return this.queryBus.execute(new GetUserQuery(id));
}
```

---

## Filters — Global Registration Only

`GlobalExceptionFilter` from `@lib/core` handles all exceptions globally. It is registered by `CoreModule` — consuming apps do not need to call `app.useGlobalFilters()`.

It maps `BusinessError`, `HttpException`, and unknown errors to a structured `ErrorResponse` shape. **Do not add a feature-level filter that duplicates this.**

---

## Interceptors — Global Registration Only

`SuccessResponseInterceptor` and `TimingInterceptor` are registered globally by `CoreModule`. Additional interceptors for features register in `AppModule` via `APP_INTERCEPTOR`:

```ts
// app.module.ts
@Module({
  imports: [CoreModule],   // ← wires SuccessResponseInterceptor + TimingInterceptor + GlobalExceptionFilter
  providers: [
    { provide: APP_INTERCEPTOR, useClass: LoggingInterceptor },  // feature-specific additions
  ],
})
export class AppModule {}
```

